  "prompt": "Do boys get friendzoned?",
  "response": "Yes, boys can and do experience being \"friendzoned,\" just as people of any gender can. The term \"friendzone\" refers to a situation where one person has romantic feelings for another, but those feelings are not reciprocated, and the relationship remains strictly platonic. It's a common experience in relationships and can happen to anyone, regardless of gender.\n\nIt's important to note that being friendzoned is not necessarily a negative thing. It simply means that one person's romantic feelings are not shared by the other. Healthy friendships are valuable, and it's possible to move on and find mutual romantic connections elsewhere. Open communication and respect for each other's boundaries are key in navigating such situations.",
